which is the same data set we used in the previous tutorials.

00:05:20.000 --> 00:05:28.000
The black dot here represents the mean of FVC, and the blue lines represent the 

00:05:28.000 --> 00:05:32.000
confidence interval, and the red lines represent the prediction interval

00:05:33.000 --> 00:05:41.000
around the mean, we can see that the prediction interval is wider than the confidence interval to capture individual 

00:05:41.000 --> 00:05:43.000
variations. 

00:05:44.000 --> 00:05:49.000
The interpretation of these two intervals is, for the confidence interval,

00:05:50.000 --> 00:05:55.000
we say if we were to take many samples and calculate the confidence interval for each sample,

00:05:56.000 --> 00:06:01.000
about 95% of those intervals would contain the true mean FVC of smokers.

00:06:03.000 --> 00:06:09.000
This interval only reflects uncertainty around the mean FVC, not individual values.

00:06:10.000 --> 00:06:12.000
For the prediction interval,

00:06:12.000 --> 00:06:19.000
we say 95% of FVC for an individual smoker will fall within this interval if sampled repeatedly.

00:06:21.000 --> 00:06:25.000
This interval reflects uncertainty around an individual measurement,

00:06:26.000 --> 00:06:27.000
not the group's average.

